🛠 CODE_EXECUTOR [advisory]:
  Edge (web):
    - code_task: graceful degradation — returns helpful message suggesting CLI
    - code_review: routed to claude executor (can reason about code without filesystem)

  Task Runner (scripts/taskrunner.sh — autonomous overnight sessions):
    - Polls: GET /api/cc-tasks/next for pending tasks (respects dependencies + priority)
    - Spawns: claude -p "<mission_brief>" --dangerously-skip-permissions --output-format json --max-turns N --settings hooks/autonomous-settings.json
    - Mission brief includes: task instructions, no-questions constraint, no-deploy constraint, completion signal
    - Safety hooks: block AskUserQuestion, block destructive ops, block deploys, block secret access, post-edit syntax check
    - Results posted back: POST /api/cc-tasks/:id/complete with result/error/exit_code
    - Session digest auto-posted after each task for dreaming cycle ingestion
    - Modes: --max N (task limit), --loop (poll forever), --dry-run (preview)
    - Queue management: MCP tools (aegis_create_cc_task) or REST API (POST /api/cc-tasks)

  Local (daemon):
    - Spawns: claude --print --output-format json --max-budget-usd <budget> --model sonnet
    - code_review: read-only tools (Read, Glob, Grep, git log/diff), $0.50 budget
    - code_task on CLI: full tools, $2.00 budget
    - code_task on non-CLI: read-only tools (safety)
    - Repo resolution: semantic memory topic matching
    - Env: strips CLAUDECODE + CLAUDE_CODE_ENTRYPOINT to avoid nesting guard
    - Timeout: 5 minutes

🔭 SELF_IMPROVEMENT [advisory]:
  GitHub in-process tools (web channel, 11 tools, available when GITHUB_TOKEN + GITHUB_REPO set):
    Read:
    - list_org_repos: GET /orgs/{org}/repos → name/visibility/language/updated_at (default: org from GITHUB_REPO)
    - list_repo_files: GET /git/trees/HEAD?recursive=1 → flat file path list
    - read_repo_file: GET /contents/{path} → base64-decoded, truncated at 8000 chars (shows total size)
    - get_repo_commits: GET /commits → sha/message/author/date (first-line message)
    - get_repo_issues: GET /issues → filters out PRs, returns number/title/state/url/labels
    - get_repo_prs: GET /pulls → number/title/state/merged/head/base/url
    - get_ci_status: GET /commits/{ref}/status + /actions/runs → combined commit status + Actions workflow runs

    Write:
    - create_improvement_issue: POST /issues + addAgendaItem mirror
    - create_improvement_pr: single-file: createBranch → updateFile → createPullRequest + addAgendaItem(high)
    - create_multi_file_pr: multi-file: createBranch → createBlob(each) → createTree → createGitCommit → updateRef → createPullRequest + addAgendaItem(high)
    - merge_pull_request: PUT /pulls/{n}/merge (squash/merge/rebase) + auto-resolve matching agenda item

  Classification: 'self_improvement' → claude executor (via DEFAULT_ROUTES in router.ts)

  Triggers:
    - On-demand: chat message classified as self_improvement by Groq
    - Scheduled: runSelfImprovementAnalysis() in kernel/scheduled.ts
      - Runs at UTC hours divisible by 6 (00, 06, 12, 18) — 4x per day max
      - Skips silently if GITHUB_TOKEN/GITHUB_REPO not set
      - Activity-gated: skips if no new episodes or commits since last run

  Feedback loop (recordSelfImprovementOutcomes):
    - Checks closed PRs with aegis/ branch prefix — distinguishes merged vs closed-without-merge
    - Records outcome facts to self_improvement_outcomes memory topic

  Cost constraints:
    - 8000 char truncation per file read (~2000 tokens)
    - Scheduled prompt caps output at 2-3 issues/PRs per run
    - Self-improvement failure is caught + logged, never propagates to runScheduledTasks

  Resilience:
    - ghFetch retries transient 500/502/503 with exponential backoff (2 retries, 500ms base)
    - Rate limit detection: 403 (primary) and 429 (secondary) with descriptive errors
    - createBranch catches 422 → clear "branch already exists" error

  Required GitHub token scopes: repo (or fine-grained: Contents read/write, Issues write, Pull requests write, Actions read, Metadata read)
  Secret: GITHUB_TOKEN — set via `wrangler secret put GITHUB_TOKEN --name aegis-web`
  Var: GITHUB_REPO = "Stackbilt-dev/aegis" (in wrangler.toml [vars])

🔌 MCP_SERVER_ENDPOINT [advisory]:
  Stateless remote MCP server at /mcp — exposes AEGIS tools to external MCP clients (Claude Code, Claude Desktop, etc.).
  Protocol: MCP 2025-03-26 over Streamable HTTP (JSON-RPC 2.0, stateless — no Durable Objects)
  Auth: Bearer AEGIS_TOKEN (same middleware as all other endpoints)
  Implementation: web/src/mcp-server.ts — direct JSON-RPC handler (no SDK dependencies)
  Route: app.all('/mcp') in web/src/index.ts

  Tools (15 total — 8 read, 7 write):
    Read:
    - aegis_chat: Full kernel dispatch (classify → route → execute), returns response + metadata
    - aegis_conversations: List recent conversations (limit param, max 50)
    - aegis_conversation_history: Get messages for a conversation
    - aegis_agenda: Active agenda items + proposed actions
    - aegis_health: Service health + procedure stats
    - aegis_memory: Semantic memory entries (optional topic filter)
    - aegis_list_goals: Active autonomous goals with schedule + run count
    - aegis_cc_sessions: Claude Code session digests (by ID or recent)
    - aegis_list_cc_tasks: List queued CC tasks (optional status filter)

    Write (direct D1, bypasses kernel routing — for Claude Code parity):
    - aegis_record_memory: Write semantic memory entry (topic, fact, confidence, source)
    - aegis_add_agenda: Add agenda item (item, context, priority)
    - aegis_resolve_agenda: Resolve agenda item as done/dismissed
    - aegis_add_goal: Create autonomous goal (title, description, schedule_hours)
    - aegis_update_goal: Pause/complete/fail a goal
    - aegis_create_cc_task: Queue a Claude Code task for autonomous execution (title, repo, prompt, priority, depends_on, max_turns)
    - aegis_cancel_cc_task: Cancel a pending CC task

  Client config (Claude Code .claude/settings.json):
    { "mcpServers": { "aegis": { "type": "url", "url": "https://aegis-web.kurt-5be.workers.dev/mcp", "headers": { "Authorization": "Bearer <AEGIS_TOKEN>" } } } }

🔐 SECURITY [load-bearing]:
  - CLI channel: full tool access (god mode — user is at keyboard)
  - Web channel: elevated BizOps + memory, no filesystem. code_task degrades gracefully.
  - Slack channel: read-only BizOps + web search only (deferred)
  - Edge Worker: Bearer auth on all endpoints (cookie/header/query param)
  - MCP: Bearer token auth, never exposed in URLs
